temperament: Self assured and moderately active, German Shepherds are willing to learn and eager to have a purpose. They're curious, can become over protective. Highly intelligent and obedient.
description: A working dog of medium to large size. The German Shepherd was originally bred as a herding dog, for herding sheep. They've since been used in many types of work including disability assistance, search-and-rescure, police work, and warfare.
